<p><b>Alain de Botton</b>, (born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1969-12-20"><a href="/wiki/December_20" title="December 20">20 December</a> <a href="/wiki/1969" title="1969">1969</a></span> in <a href="/wiki/Zurich" title="Zurich" class="mw-redirect">Zurich</a>, <a href="/wiki/Switzerland" title="Switzerland">Switzerland</a>) is a British writer and television producer. His books and television programmes discuss various subjects in a somewhat <a href="/wiki/Philosophy" title="Philosophy">philosophical</a> style while maintaining relevance to everyday life. In August 2008, he was a founder member of a new educational establishment in central London called <i>The School of Life</i>.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-OfficialBio_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-OfficialBio-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
